From c35c36f990e4b8974e2d4e006116ff3e8e2e7d78 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Richard <Richard.Zhang@cybertan.com.tw>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 17:20:13 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] mediatek: add support for Sonicfi Rap630w-211g

MT7981B-based AP with MT7976 radios. Two-slot rootfs scheme:
the vendor U-Boot passes the active slot and partition names in
'boot_param.*' kernel cmdline variables; sysupgrade reads those
via cmdline_get_var, writes to the inactive slot, and updates the
u-boot environment to flip the active-slot pointer.

  * device tree under target/linux/mediatek/dts/
  * board.d/02_network entry for interface layout (lan1-3 + eth1)
    and label MAC seeding from u-boot env 'ethaddr'
  * filogic/base-files/lib/upgrade/platform.sh: dual-slot
    nand_do_upgrade path using cmdline_get_var to discover
    boot_param.upgrade_kernel_part / upgrade_rootfs_part /
    upgrade_image_slot, then driving fw_setenv via CI_FWSETENV
    to commit the new active slot. Default
    nand_do_platform_check is used unchanged.
  * uboot-envtools/files/mediatek_filogic: discover the env UBI
    volume at runtime from 'boot_param.env_part' on the kernel
    cmdline and register it with ubootenv_add_uci_config
  * target/linux/mediatek/image/filogic.mk: Device/ block opting
    into DEVICE_FIT_ROOTFS_HASH (vendor U-Boot reads the rootfs
    size/crc32/sha1 from the top-level FIT 'rootfs' node before
    mounting the on-flash rootfs partition)

Signed-off-by: John Crispin <john@phrozen.org>
---
